      "created_at": "2026-06-11T20:49:28Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-11T20:49:28Z",
      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "Because `ReadRawBlock()` reads the full byte count stored in the block-file record.\n\nIf those bytes deserialize to a valid `CBlock` but leave extra bytes unused, the record is malformed. Today `ReadBlock()` silently ignores those leftover bytes and then validates only the deserialized prefix.\n\nThis check makes `ReadBlock()` reject that malformed record instead of treating it as a successful block read. It should not affect valid blocks, because valid block records are fully consumed by `TX_WITH_WITNESS(block)`.",
      "user": {
        "login": "OSINTv96",
        "id": 175096749,
        "node_id": "U_kgDOCm_DrQ",
        "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/175096749?v=4",
